{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a37da055-6c37-49db-a9c7-1e42c1dfed5d","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 drops support for older target frameworks.** Specifically:\n\n- **`net462`** — ❌ Not supported. MSTest v3 requires at least .NET Framework **4.7.2** (`net472`).\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — ❌ Not supported. MSTest v3 requires at least **.NET 6.0** (`net6.0`).\n- **`net5.0`** — ❌ Not supported. .NET 5 is out of support; MSTest v3 requires `net6.0`+.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to supported versions, e.g.:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net472</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\nAlso, MSTest v3 consolidates packages into a single `MSTest` meta-package, replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7a029ee7-fdda-4f0b-a51b-422954426059","outputTokens":265,"requestId":"5837:31143A:168FCF1:17EF129:6A04605B"},"id":"5db25432-64c9-44f6-8f9b-663bb2afbfac","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:28:37.315Z","parentId":"015ea0fb-b6b9-42cf-8ea3-e63220408474"}
